  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Response and Prevention of Gender Based Violence (GBV) against Refugees Focusing on Women, Children and Vulnerable Persons in Kampala, Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees: Women, Children, Other Vulnerable Persons</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to achieve its objectives by providing psychosocial services in the form of individual and group therapy sessions, performing home visits to identify the clients&#x2019; needs, referring clients to partners,  disseminating information on reporting SGBV and children&#x2019;s rights at monthly community dialogues, publishing desk calendars with SGBV messages, putting on drama shows with SGBV messages,  creating posters and t-shirts with SGBV messages, conducting peer-to-peer discussions on SGBV topics with beneficiaries, commemoration of international SGBV days,  provide children with monthly awareness sessions, and hosting a sports gala for refugee youth.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to improve the psychological and social well-being of refugees focusing on women, children and vulnerable persons. The project has three main objectives. The first is to improve the psychological and social well-being of refugees focusing on women, children and vulnerable persons through provision of psychological counseling and social services in individual and group settings. The second is to improve the quality of response and to raise community awareness on SGBV issues resulting in a more protective environment for refugees, particularly women and vulnerable persons affected by SGBV. The third is to strengthen the protection of refugee children on SGBV issues by increasing awareness of children&#x2019;s rights among community members.</narrative>
  </description>
